701 (1)a. The personal knowledge of the notary public of
702 the identity of the signatory.
703 (2)a.b.1. The presentation of two valid forms of
704 government issued identification, one of which shall include
705 the face and signature of the signatory; and.
706 b.2. A process by which the notary public verifies the
707 identity of the signatory through a review of public or
708 private data sources.
709 (2) The remote notary shall verify that the remotely
